    "csaf_version": "2.0",
    "notes": [
      {
        "category": "summary",
        "text": "An update is available for libsndfile.\nThis update affects Rocky Linux 9.\nA Common Vulnerability Scoring System (CVSS) base score, which gives a detailed severity rating, is available for each vulnerability from the CVE list",
        "title": "Topic"
      },
      {
        "category": "description",
        "text": "libsndfile is a C library for reading and writing files containing sampled sound, such as AIFF, AU, or WAV. \n\nSecurity Fix(es):\n\n* libsndfile: Segmentation fault error in ogg_vorbis.c:417 vorbis_analysis_wrote() (CVE-2024-50612)\n\nFor more details about the security issue(s), including the impact, a CVSS score, acknowledgments, and other related information, refer to the CVE page(s) listed in the References section.\n\nThis advisory is provided by Ctrl IQ, Inc for Rocky Linux systems. For more information about CIQ security practices, visit https://ciq.com/security.",
        "title": "Description"
      }
    ],
